"title": "5366: king",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5366: king",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The ruler or monarch of a country or realm. God is king of all the earth and human kings are called to rule in accordance with his will. The failure of kings in Israel and Judah after David led to the expectation of a coming king like David. This was fulfilled in Jesus Christ: the true King of Israel and all the world.</p>\n<h2>God is king of his people and of all the earth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:8\">PSA 47:8</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew refers to the rule of a king</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15-1Tim6:16\">1TI 6:15–6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:18\">EXO 15:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:12\">1SA 12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:6\">2CH 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps24:10\">PSA 24:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:2\">PSA 47:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:6-Ps47:7\">PSA 47:6–47:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps93:1\">PSA 93:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:10\">PSA 96:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:1\">PSA 97:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:1\">PSA 99:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:5\">ISA 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:6\">ISA 44:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3\">REV 15:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:6\">REV 19:6</a></p>\n<h2>Significant kings</h2>\n<h3>Melchizedek, king of Salem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:18\">GEN 14:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:6\">HEB 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:10\">HEB 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:20-Heb7:17\">HEB 6:20–7:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:4\">PSA 110:4</a></p>\n<h3>The Pharaohs, the kings of Egypt</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:14-Gen12:20\">GEN 12:14–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:39-Gen41:40\">GEN 41:39–41:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:30-Exod12:32\">EXO 12:30–12:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:4\">EXO 14:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:1\">1KI 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:29\">2KI 23:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:33-2Kgs23:34\">2KI 23:33–23:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:1-Ezek32:10\">EZK 32:1–32:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:17\">ROM 9:17</a></p>\n<h3>Saul</h3>\n<p>Israel's demand for a king is seen as a rejection of God's rule:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:4-1Sam8:9\">1SA 8:4–8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:19-1Sam8:22\">1SA 8:19–8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:17-1Sam10:19\">1SA 10:17–10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:12-1Sam12:15\">1SA 12:12–12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:1-1Sam9:2\">1SA 9:1–9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:24\">1SA 10:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:14-1Sam11:15\">1SA 11:14–11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:1\">1SA 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:11-1Sam13:14\">1SA 13:11–13:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:17\">1SA 15:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:26\">1SA 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:1-1Sam31:4\">1SA 31:1–31:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:1-1Chr10:4\">1CH 10:1–10:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:13-1Chr10:14\">1CH 10:13–10:14</a></p>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:26-1Chr29:28\">1CH 29:26–29:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:10-1Kgs2:12\">1KI 2:10–2:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:3-2Sam5:5\">2SA 5:3–5:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:3\">1CH 11:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:1-2Sam8:14\">2SA 8:1–8:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr18:1-1Chr18:13\">1CH 18:1–18:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:38\">1KI 11:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:50\">PSA 18:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70-Ps78:722\">PSA 78:70–78:722</a>SA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:8-Ps7:16\">7:8–7:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:7-1Chr17:14\">1CH 17:7–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:4-1Kgs9:5\">1KI 9:4–9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:17-2Chr7:18\">2CH 7:17–7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:11-Ps132:12\">PSA 132:11–132:12</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:24-2Sam12:25\">2SA 12:24–12:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:12\">1KI 2:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:1\">2CH 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:29-1Kgs4:34\">1KI 4:29–4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:1\">1KI 6:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:1\">2CH 3:1</a> <em>Solomon began to build the temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:23-1Kgs10:25\">1KI 10:23–10:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:22-2Chr9:24\">2CH 9:22–9:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:1\">1KI 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:4\">1KI 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:42-1Kgs11:43\">1KI 11:42–11:43</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:30-2Chr9:31\">2CH 9:30–9:31</a> <em>Solomon's death</em></p>\n<h3>Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:1\">2KI 24:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:6-2Chr36:7\">2CH 36:6–36:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:1\">2KI 25:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:17\">2CH 36:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:1\">JER 39:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:4\">JER 52:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:1\">DAN 1:1</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer21:7\">JER 21:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:6\">JER 27:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:8\">JER 27:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek29:18-Ezek29:19\">EZK 29:18–29:19</a> <em>Nebuchadnezzar besieged Tyre for 15 years</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:1\">DAN 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:46-Dan2:47\">DAN 2:46–2:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:1\">DAN 3:1</a> <em>the image of gold</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:28-Dan3:29\">DAN 3:28–3:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:28-Dan4:37\">DAN 4:28–4:37</a></p>\n<h3>Cyrus, king of Persia</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:22-2Chr36:23\">2CH 36:22–36:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:1-Ezra1:4\">EZR 1:1–1:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:13-Ezra6:5\">EZR 5:13–6:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:28-Isa45:1\">ISA 44:28–45:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:13\">ISA 45:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:28\">DAN 6:28</a></p>\n<h3>The Herods, rulers in Palestine</h3>\n<p>Herod the Great:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:1-Matt2:3\">MAT 2:1–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:16\">MAT 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:1-Matt14:2\">MAT 14:1–14:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:14-Mark6:16\">MRK 6:14–6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:7-Luke9:9\">LUK 9:7–9:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:15\">MRK 8:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:19-Luke3:20\">LUK 3:19–3:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:31\">LUK 13:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:7-Luke23:12\">LUK 23:7–23:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:27\">ACT 4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:1-Acts12:4\">ACT 12:1–12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:19-Acts12:23\">ACT 12:19–12:23</a></p>\n<h2>The kings of the united kingdom</h2>\n<h3>Saul</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:20-1Sam10:24\">1SA 10:20–10:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:12-1Sam11:15\">1SA 11:12–11:15</a></p>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:1-2Sam2:4\">2SA 2:1–2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:1-2Sam5:5\">2SA 5:1–5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:11\">1KI 2:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:1-1Chr29:30\">1CH 11:1–29:30</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:39\">1KI 1:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:1-2Chr9:31\">2CH 1:1–9:31</a></p>\n<h2>The kings of Israel, the northern kingdom</h2>\n<h3>Jeroboam I</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:20\">1KI 12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:25-1Kgs14:20\">1KI 12:25–14:20</a></p>\n<h3>Nadab</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:25-1Kgs15:31\">1KI 15:25–15:31</a></p>\n<h3>Baasha</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:32-1Kgs16:7\">1KI 15:32–16:7</a></p>\n<h3>Elah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:8-1Kgs16:14\">1KI 16:8–16:14</a></p>\n<h3>Zimri</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:15-1Kgs16:20\">1KI 16:15–16:20</a></p>\n<h3>Tibni</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:21-1Kgs16:22\">1KI 16:21–16:22</a></p>\n<h3>Omri</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:23-1Kgs16:28\">1KI 16:23–16:28</a></p>\n<h3>Ahab</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:29-1Kgs22:40\">1KI 16:29–22:40</a></p>\n<h3>Ahaziah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:51-1Kgs22:53\">1KI 22:51–22:53</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:1-2Kgs1:18\">2KI 1:1–1:18</a></p>\n<h3>Joram (Jehoram)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:1-2Kgs8:15\">2KI 3:1–8:15</a></p>\n<h3>Jehu</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:3-2Kgs10:36\">2KI 9:3–10:36</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoahaz</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:1-2Kgs13:9\">2KI 13:1–13:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoash (Joash)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:10-2Kgs13:25\">2KI 13:10–13:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:8-2Kgs14:16\">2KI 14:8–14:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jeroboam II</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:23-2Kgs14:29\">2KI 14:23–14:29</a></p>\n<h3>Zechariah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:8-2Kgs15:12\">2KI 15:8–15:12</a></p>\n<h3>Shallum</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:13-2Kgs15:15\">2KI 15:13–15:15</a></p>\n<h3>Menahem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:16-2Kgs15:22\">2KI 15:16–15:22</a></p>\n<h3>Pekahiah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:23-2Kgs15:26\">2KI 15:23–15:26</a></p>\n<h3>Pekah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:27-2Kgs15:31\">2KI 15:27–15:31</a></p>\n<h3>Hoshea</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:1-2Kgs17:6\">2KI 17:1–17:6</a></p>\n<h2>The kings and queen of Judah, the southern kingdom</h2>\n<h3>Rehoboam</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:1-1Kgs12:24\">1KI 12:1–12:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:1-2Chr11:4\">2CH 10:1–11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:5-2Chr12:8\">2CH 11:5–12:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:21-1Kgs14:31\">1KI 14:21–14:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:9-2Chr12:16\">2CH 12:9–12:16</a></p>\n<h3>Abijah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:1-1Kgs15:8\">1KI 15:1–15:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:1-2Chr14:1\">2CH 13:1–14:1</a></p>\n<h3>Asa</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:9-1Kgs15:24\">1KI 15:9–15:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:2-2Chr16:14\">2CH 14:2–16:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoshaphat</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:41-1Kgs22:50\">1KI 22:41–22:50</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:31-2Chr21:1\">2CH 20:31–21:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:1-2Chr21:3\">2CH 17:1–21:3</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoram (Joram)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:16-2Kgs8:24\">2KI 8:16–8:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr21:4-2Chr21:20\">2CH 21:4–21:20</a></p>\n<h3>Ahaziah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs8:25-2Kgs8:29\">2KI 8:25–8:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:1-2Chr22:6\">2CH 22:1–22:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:21-2Kgs9:29\">2KI 9:21–9:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:7-2Chr22:9\">2CH 22:7–22:9</a></p>\n<h3>Queen Athaliah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:1-2Kgs11:21\">2KI 11:1–11:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:10-2Chr23:21\">2CH 22:10–23:21</a></p>\n<h3>Joash (Jehoash)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:2-2Kgs12:21\">2KI 11:2–12:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:10-2Chr24:27\">2CH 22:10–24:27</a></p>\n<h3>Amaziah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:1-2Kgs14:22\">2KI 14:1–14:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:1-2Chr25:28\">2CH 25:1–25:28</a></p>\n<h3>Azariah (= Uzziah)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:21-2Kgs14:22\">2KI 14:21–14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:1-2Kgs15:7\">2KI 15:1–15:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:1-2Chr26:23\">2CH 26:1–26:23</a></p>\n<h3>Jotham</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:32-2Kgs15:38\">2KI 15:32–15:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr27:1-2Chr27:9\">2CH 27:1–27:9</a></p>\n<h3>Ahaz</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:1-2Kgs16:20\">2KI 16:1–16:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:1-2Chr28:27\">2CH 28:1–28:27</a></p>\n<h3>Hezekiah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:1-2Kgs20:21\">2KI 18:1–20:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:1-2Chr32:33\">2CH 29:1–32:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:1-Isa39:8\">ISA 36:1–39:8</a></p>\n<h3>Manasseh</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:1-2Kgs21:18\">2KI 21:1–21:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:1-2Chr33:20\">2CH 33:1–33:20</a></p>\n<h3>Amon</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:19-2Kgs21:26\">2KI 21:19–21:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:21-2Chr33:25\">2CH 33:21–33:25</a></p>\n<h3>Josiah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:1-2Kgs23:30\">2KI 22:1–23:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:1-2Chr35:27\">2CH 34:1–35:27</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoahaz</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:31-2Kgs23:34\">2KI 23:31–23:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:2-2Chr36:4\">2CH 36:2–36:4</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoiakim</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:36-2Kgs24:6\">2KI 23:36–24:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:5-2Chr36:8\">2CH 36:5–36:8</a></p>\n<h3>Jehoiachin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:8-2Kgs24:17\">2KI 24:8–24:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:9-2Chr36:10\">2CH 36:9–36:10</a></p>\n<h3>Zedekiah (= Mattaniah)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:18-2Kgs25:7\">2KI 24:18–25:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:11-2Chr36:21\">2CH 36:11–36:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:1-Jer52:11\">JER 52:1–52:11</a></p>\n<h2>The expectation of a future king like David</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:5\">ISA 11:1–11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:5\">ISA 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:8-Jer30:9\">JER 30:8–30:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:15\">JER 33:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23-Ezek34:24\">EZK 34:23–34:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:24-Ezek37:25\">EZK 37:24–37:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:11\">AMO 9:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2-Mic5:5\">MIC 5:2–5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:20-Hag2:23\">HAG 2:20–2:23</a></p>\n<h2>The duties of the king</h2>\n<h3>To fear God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:3-2Sam23:4\">2SA 23:3–23:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:28\">PRO 20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:14-Deut17:20\">DEU 17:14–17:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:25\">1SA 10:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:10-Ps2:11\">PSA 2:10–2:11</a></p>\n<h3>To maintain righteousness and administer justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:4\">PRO 29:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:14\">PRO 29:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:28\">1KI 3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:1-Ps72:4\">PSA 72:1–72:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:12-Prov16:13\">PRO 16:12–16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:8\">PRO 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:26\">PRO 20:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:4-Prov31:5\">PRO 31:4–31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:8-Prov31:9\">PRO 31:8–31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:4\">ISA 11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:15\">JER 33:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:4\">ROM 13:4</a></p>\n<h3>To read the law of God and ensure it was obeyed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:18-Deut17:20\">DEU 17:18–17:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:1-1Kgs2:4\">1KI 2:1–2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:4-1Kgs9:5\">1KI 9:4–9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:12\">2KI 11:12</a></p>\n<h2>The coronation of the king</h2>\n<h3>His anointing by the prophet of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1-1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:1–16:13</a></p>\n<h3>His proclamation as king before the people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:12\">2KI 11:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:11\">2CH 23:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:17-1Sam10:25\">1SA 10:17–10:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:15\">1SA 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:4\">2SA 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:1-2Sam5:3\">2SA 5:1–5:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:1-1Chr11:3\">1CH 11:1–11:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:10\">2SA 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:28-1Kgs1:40\">1KI 1:28–1:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:1\">1KI 12:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:1\">2CH 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:20\">1KI 12:20</a></p>\n<h3>Royal Psalms</h3>\n<p>These Psalms, although used in honour of the king of the day, possibly at his coronation, share the expectation of a greater king. The NT regards them as fulfilled in Jesus Christ:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:6-Ps2:9\">PSA 2:6–2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:1\">PSA 45:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:1\">PSA 72:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:10\">PSA 132:10</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is the true King of Israel and of the world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:37\">MAT 27:37</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:26\">MRK 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:38\">LUK 23:38</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:49\">JHN 1:49</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:5\">MAT 21:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:2\">MRK 15:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:11\">MAT 27:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:3\">LUK 23:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:36-John18:37\">JHN 18:36–18:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:7\">ACT 17:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:25\">1CO 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:8\">HEB 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:6\">PSA 45:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:14\">REV 17:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:16\">REV 19:16</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ fulfils the expectation of a son of David who will be a king like David</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32-Luke1:33\">LUK 1:32–1:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:69\">LUK 1:69</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:22-Acts13:23\">ACT 13:22–13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3\">ROM 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:8\">2TI 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:5\">REV 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></p>",
